9. Financial Services in the Era of Generative AI
Publisher: Hong Kong Institute for Monetary Research (HKIMR)

Date: April 2025

Link: [HKIMR Report](https://www.aof.org.hk/docs/default-source/hkimr/applied-research-report/genairep1.pdf)

Key findings: Survey of Hong Kong financial institutions. 95% cite model accuracy/performance as top risk; 65% cite transparency/explainability; 64% cite data privacy/security. Highlights the "human-in-the-loop" challenge: vast volumes of AI outputs make manual review impossible, yet accountability demands human oversight.

For your team: The section on model-risk management (governance, validation, assessment, monitoring, mitigation) maps directly to Basel/SR 11-7 expectations.

