11. 2026 Global AI in Financial Services Report
Publisher: Cambridge Centre for Alternative Finance

Date: May 2026

Link: [Cambridge Report](https://www.jbs.cam.ac.uk/faculty-research/centres/alternative-finance/publications/2026-global-ai-in-financial-services-report/)

Key findings: Survey of 130 regulatory authorities and hundreds of firms. Data privacy (74% industry, 80% regulators) and model hallucinations (70% both) are top concerns. Critical divergence: regulators are far more worried than vendors about cyber threats, third-party concentration risk, and consumer protection. Only 50% of industry respondents have adopted explainable AI methods; about two-thirds do not monitor for bias.

For your team: The gap between regulatory expectation and industry practice on explainability/bias is a compliance time bomb. This report gives you the evidence to justify investment.

